HIV/Aids: China ta samu karuwar sabon kamuwa da cutar da kashi 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta ce yawan mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da kuma wadanda ke fama da cutar AIDS ya karu da kashi 14 cikin 100.
Mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da wannan matsalar, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya a ƙasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na shekara ta 2018 kadai, an samu kusan mutane 40,000 da suka kamu da cutar.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun kasance na jima'i, wanda ke nufin cewa an canja su daga baya.
A wasu wurare a ƙasar Sin, cutar HIV tana yaduwa da sauri ta wurin karɓar jini.
Amma, an rage yawan mutanen da suka kamu da cutar ta HIV a wannan hanyar, kamar yadda jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin suka ce a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma, a shekara guda, adadin mutanen da ke da HIV da kuma waɗanda suke da cutar AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An kawar da cin zarafin 'yan luwadi a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma ana nuna wariya ga 'yan luwadi.
Idan aka yi la'akari da yadda ƙasar ta kasance mai tsaron gida, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza za su auri wata mace a ƙarshe.
Yawancin cututtuka na cututtuka sun faru ne domin rashin tsaro a lokacin yin jima'i a cikin waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin Sin ta ba da damar samun magungunan cutar HIV a ko'ina a duniya a ƙoƙarin magance cutar.
